# LiNKaios Web UI (Next.js App Router)

## Scope

Applies to files in `apps/LiNKaios/**`.

## Architecture

- Use the **App Router** with server components by default.
- Client components only when required (stateful UI, browser APIs, event handlers).
- Prefer **Server Actions** for mutations; API routes under `app/api/*` when needed.
- Centralize environment access via a typed config module — do not read `process.env` directly in components.

## Routing

- Organize routes under `apps/LiNKaios/app/*` with clear segment folders.
- Co-locate `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, and route-specific components in the same segment.

## Styling & UI

- Tailwind CSS for all styling.
- shadcn/ui for primitives. Compose rather than fork.
- Accessibility: semantic HTML, ARIA, keyboard navigation, visible focus states.
- Mobile-first responsive layouts.
- Use Impeccable design principles: avoid generic AI-looking UI, tinted neutrals instead of pure gray, no overused fonts, no cards-inside-cards.

## Data Fetching

- Server components: fetch data directly with async/await; cache where appropriate.
- Client components: use TanStack Query for remote state with centralized query keys.
- Validate all inputs and external responses with Zod. Return typed data only.

## Auth (Supabase)

- Use Supabase Auth helpers for Next.js.
- Handle sessions on the server when possible; avoid exposing tokens to the client.
- Protect server actions and API routes with auth checks.

## Performance

- Avoid unnecessary client components.
- Use dynamic import for heavy components.
- Use `next/image` for all images.
- Enable route-level streaming where beneficial.
